**Probability computation (deterministic).** For each session in `sigma_summary.sessions`, your `prob_up_pct` must equal `Φ((daily_drift_pct × N) / one_sigma_half_width_pct)` computed under the **bounded** `daily_drift_pct` (see clamps below). The server **will recompute** this from your inputs and flag any session where the emitted probability deviates by >2 percentage points.

**`daily_drift_pct` must be sourced**, not estimated from narrative. Choose one of:
- **options_skew**: 25-delta call IV minus 25-delta put IV, mapped to ~0.5–1% drift per 100bps of skew.
- **PT_consensus**: `(consensus_PT − current_price) / days_to_PT_horizon`. Cap at 0.30%/day.
- **PEAD_avg**: average daily return over the first 5 sessions after each of the last 4 earnings windows (from `outcome_tracker`). Server-injected hints: `pead_avg_drift_pct` / `recent_momentum_drift_pct` when available.
- **recent_momentum**: 5/10/20-day average daily return.
- **manual_override**: only with explicit justification in `drift_source_value`. Server will still bound.

The server clamps |drift| to ≤ 0.15%/day for most sources (≤ 0.30%/day for PT_consensus). Drift values outside these bounds will be clamped silently and the verifier will note the adjustment.

**Do not** emit `prob_up_pct` values that imply implausible drift (e.g. 75% at T+5 with σ=14% requires drift > 0.27%/day; verifier will flag).

